      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR NOW (1) went close when resuming on the Parks track a fortnight ago and doesn't face much tougher here. Claimer stays on to help offset the big weight. Can go one better. BIANCELLI (5) is a promising mare resuming for a sharp stable. She's jumped out well leading in and boasts a strong first-up record. Sure to be very competitive. ENUFF SEDUCTION (4) will be hoping for a genuine tempo to allow his powerful turn of foot to come into play. Tootell will need to be at her best from the inside draw to avoid getting cluttered away. SIXTEEN REASONS (3) was excellent first-up when flashing home in the G3 John Hawkes Stakes here. Was less effective last time on what proved a tricky track. Willing to forgive third-up. WINNING REVOLUTION (2) doesn't win often but brings ratings that measure up and is a proven track and trip specialist. Can't leave out.",
